Nigerian, Mr. Olujimi Fafowora, has got a First Class honours degree at University of Oxford in England.  Fafowora, 21, graduated in Mathematics at St. Peter’s College, Oxford.  The Nation learnt Fafowora has become the second Nigerian to have ever made a First Class at Oxford.   U.S ‘committed to STEM education’     Tinubu on Shettima: I’ve made hard, best choice     Monarch makes case for youths in sports   Last year, he was appointed a fellow of the college and will remain at Oxford for another year pursuing his postgraduate studies.  He is the grandson of Ambassador and Mrs Dapo Fafowora. “Before Oxford, he was at Haberdashers College, a private school in London, from where he obtained nine  ‘O’ level distinctions and four ‘A’ level distinctions. We are very proud of him,” said Fafowora. Fafowora was a Commonwealth Scholar at Trinity College, Oxford, from 1969-72.